@startuml seq-tab-close
'' ============================================================================
'' vinary-viewer — Sequence: close a tab (retract the doc + stop its watcher +
'' choose the new active tab).
''
'' PlantUML over Mermaid because: the handler computes the *new* active tab
'' BEFORE retracting the entity (order matters), splits into a DataScript write
'' and an IPC close, and the `:tabs` subscription recomputes only because the
'' retraction bumps `:ds/rev`. Activation bars + an explicit `:ds/rev` note make
'' that ordering legible; Mermaid blurs the pre/post-retraction read.
'' ============================================================================
!include _vv-theme.iuml

title Close a tab — `:tab/close`

autonumber "0:"

actor User #white
participant "ui.tabs\n(× button)" as Tabs RENDERER_COLOR
participant "re-frame\nevents/fx" as RF REFRAME_COLOR
participant "app.db\n(active-path)" as Db APPDB_COLOR
participant "DataScript\nconn" as DS DATASCRIPT_COLOR
participant "preload `window.vv`" as Vv IPC_COLOR
participant "main.service" as Svc MAIN_COLOR
participant "reagent UI" as UI RENDERER_COLOR

User -> Tabs : click ×\n(`stopPropagation`)
Tabs -> RF : dispatch `[:tab/close path]`
activate RF

== compute before retract ==
RF -> DS : read `open-docs` (snapshot)
DS --> RF : ordered open docs
RF -> RF : `remaining` = open-docs ∖ {path}\n`new-active` = (active==path) ?\n  (:path (last remaining)) : active
RF -> Db : `assoc-in [:ui :active-path] new-active`

== retract + stop watcher ==
RF -> DS : `:ds/transact`\n`[[:db/retractEntity eid]]`  (when eid)
RF -> Vv : `:vv/close path`
deactivate RF
Vv -> Svc : `ipcRenderer.send` **vv:close**
Svc -> Svc : `close!` — stop chokidar\nwatcher, `dissoc` from `watchers`

== reactive recompute ==
DS -> RF : `d/listen!` → `[:ds/changed]`\n(`:ds/rev` ++)
RF -> UI : `:tabs` recomputes (one fewer tab)
RF -> UI : `:doc/active` recomputes\n(reads new active-path)
UI -> UI : tab-strip re-renders;\nif no tabs ⟶ watermark

note over RF, DS
  The entity is **fully retracted** — closing a tab discards
  the document's cached HTML/text from DataScript. Re-opening
  re-reads + re-renders from disk.
end note

legend right
  |= Colour |= Concept |
  | <#2D9574> | Renderer / UI |
  | <#4F97D7> | re-frame |
  | <#7590DB> | app-db (active-path) |
  | <#A45BAD> | DataScript SSOT |
  | <#B1951D> | IPC seam |
  | <#3A5BA0> | MAIN (stop watcher) |
endlegend
@enduml
